=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Perform SNAr on the azaaryl fragment, using 2-chloro-5-bromopyridine (the regioisomer matching the target ring) with 4-fluorobenzylamine to give the bromopyridinyl benzylamine intermediate Ar1–NHCH2–C6H4F. | Step 2: Protect that exocyclic NH as Boc, then do Miyaura borylation of the bromide (B2pin2, Pd) to form the corresponding pyridyl boronate ester Ar1–Bpin. | Step 3: Suzuki couple this boronate with 2,4-dichloro-5-bromopyridine to assemble the heterobiaryl core, giving 2,4-dichloro-5-(aminobenzyl-substituted pyridyl)pyridine; then remove Boc to regenerate the Ar1–NHCH2–C6H4F group. | Step 4: Displace the more activated 2-chloro of that dichloropyridine by SNAr with trans-methyl 4-aminocyclohexane-1-carboxylate to give the methyl ester of the target skeleton, retaining the 4-chloro substituent on the central pyridine. | Step 5: Hydrolyze the methyl ester to the carboxylic acid to furnish O=C(O)[C@H]1CC[C@@H](Nc2cc(-c3cccc(NCc4cccc(F)c4)n3)c(Cl)cn2)C1.

